Burnet Institute › au › people › 66_...Professor Brendan Crabb AC | Burnet InstituteBackground. Professor Brendan Crabb AC PhD FAHMS FASM is an infectious disease researcher with a special interest in malaria. His research group develops and exploits genetic approaches to better understand malaria parasite biology, principally to help prioritise vaccine and drug targets.
